tool.name: MSGFPlusAdapter
tool.command:
ln -s $param_in ./param_in.$param_in.ext && ln -s $param_database ./param_database.$param_database.ext &&
MSGFPlusAdapter -executable /usr/local/tools/msgfplus/default/msgfplus.jar
#if $param_in: -in ./param_in.$param_in.ext #end if #if $param_out: -out $param_out #end if #if $param_mzid_out: -mzid_out $param_mzid_out #end if #if $param_database: -database ./param_database.$param_database.ext #end if #if $param_add_decoys: -add_decoys #end if #if $param_precursor_mass_tolerance: -precursor_mass_tolerance $param_precursor_mass_tolerance #end if #if $param_precursor_error_units: -precursor_error_units #if " " in str($param_precursor_error_units): "$param_precursor_error_units" #else $param_precursor_error_units #end if #end if #if $param_isotope_error_range: -isotope_error_range "$param_isotope_error_range" #end if #if $param_fragment_method: -fragment_method #if " " in str($param_fragment_method): "$param_fragment_method" #else $param_fragment_method #end if #end if #if $param_instrument: -instrument #if " " in str($param_instrument): "$param_instrument" #else $param_instrument #end if #end if #if $param_enzyme: -enzyme #if " " in str($param_enzyme): "$param_enzyme" #else $param_enzyme #end if #end if #if $param_protocol: -protocol #if " " in str($param_protocol): "$param_protocol" #else $param_protocol #end if #end if #if $param_tryptic: -tryptic #if " " in str($param_tryptic): "$param_tryptic" #else $param_tryptic #end if #end if #if $param_min_precursor_charge: -min_precursor_charge $param_min_precursor_charge #end if #if $param_max_precursor_charge: -max_precursor_charge $param_max_precursor_charge #end if #if $param_min_peptide_length: -min_peptide_length $param_min_peptide_length #end if #if $param_max_peptide_length: -max_peptide_length $param_max_peptide_length #end if #if $param_matches_per_spec: -matches_per_spec $param_matches_per_spec #end if #if $param_add_features: -add_features #end if #if $param_max_mods: -max_mods $param_max_mods #end if
#if $rep_param_fixed_modifications: -fixed_modifications #for token in $rep_param_fixed_modifications: #if " " in str(token): "$token.param_fixed_modifications" #else $token.param_fixed_modifications #end if #end for #end if
#if $rep_param_variable_modifications: -variable_modifications #for token in $rep_param_variable_modifications: #if " " in str(token): "$token.param_variable_modifications" #else $token.param_variable_modifications #end if #end for #end if #if $param_java_memory: -java_memory $param_java_memory #end if -threads \${GALAXY_SLOTS:-24} #if $adv_opts.adv_opts_selector=='advanced': #if $adv_opts.param_java_permgen: -java_permgen $adv_opts.param_java_permgen #end if #if $adv_opts.param_force: -force #end if #end if

param.label: Input file (MS-GF+ parameter '-s')
param.name: param_in

param.help: (-database) Non-existing relative filenames are looked up via 'OpenMS.ini:id_db_dir'
param.label: Protein sequence database (FASTA file; MS-GF+ parameter '-d')
param.name: param_database

param.help: (-add_decoys) This allows the calculation of FDRs, but should only be used if the database does not already contain decoys
param.label: Create decoy proteins (reversed sequences) and append them to the database for the search (MS-GF+ parameter '-tda')
param.name: param_add_decoys

param.label: Precursor monoisotopic mass tolerance (MS-GF+ parameter '-t')
param.name: param_precursor_mass_tolerance

param.label: Unit of precursor mass tolerance (MS-GF+ parameter '-t')
param.name: param_precursor_error_units

param.help: (-isotope_error_range) Takes into account the error introduced by choosing a non-monoisotopic peak for fragmentation. Combined with 'precursor_mass_tolerance'/'precursor_error_units', this determines the actual precursor mass tolerance. E.g. for experimental mass 'exp' and calculated mass 'calc', '-precursor_mass_tolerance 20 -precursor_error_units ppm -isotope_error_range -1,2' tests '|exp - calc - n * 1.00335 Da| < 20 ppm' for n = -1, 0, 1, 2
param.label: Range of allowed isotope peak errors (MS-GF+ parameter '-ti')
param.name: param_isotope_error_range

param.label: Fragmentation method ('from_spectrum' relies on spectrum meta data and uses CID as fallback option; MS-GF+ parameter '-m')
param.name: param_fragment_method

param.label: Instrument that generated the data ('low_res'/'high_res' refer to LCQ and LTQ instruments; MS-GF+ parameter '-inst')
param.name: param_instrument

param.label: Enzyme used for digestion, or type of cleavage (MS-GF+ parameter '-e')
param.name: param_enzyme

param.label: Labeling or enrichment protocol used, if any (MS-GF+ parameter '-p')
param.name: param_protocol

param.label: Level of cleavage specificity required (MS-GF+ parameter '-ntt')
param.name: param_tryptic

param.label: Minimum precursor ion charge (MS-GF+ parameter '-minCharge')
param.name: param_min_precursor_charge

param.label: Maximum precursor ion charge (MS-GF+ parameter '-maxCharge')
param.name: param_max_precursor_charge

param.label: Minimum peptide length to consider (MS-GF+ parameter '-minLength')
param.name: param_min_peptide_length

param.label: Maximum peptide length to consider (MS-GF+ parameter '-maxLength')
param.name: param_max_peptide_length

param.label: Number of matches per spectrum to be reported (MS-GF+ parameter '-n')
param.name: param_matches_per_spec

param.help: (-add_features) e.g. by Percolator (default: basic scores only; MS-GF+ parameter '-addFeatures')
param.label: Output additional features - needed
param.name: param_add_features

param.help: (-max_mods) If this value is large, the search may take very long
param.label: Maximum number of modifications per peptide
param.name: param_max_mods

param.label: Fixed modifications, specified using UniMod (www.unimod.org) terms,
param.name: param_fixed_modifications

param.label: Variable modifications, specified using UniMod (www.unimod.org) terms,
param.name: param_variable_modifications

param.label: Maximum Java heap size (in MB)
param.name: param_java_memory

param.label: Maximum Java permanent generation space (in MB); only for Java 7 and below
param.name: param_java_permgen

param.label: Overwrite tool specific checks
param.name: param_force

tool.help:
MS/MS database search using MS-GF+.
For more information, visit http://ftp.mi.fu-berlin.de/OpenMS/release-documentation/html/TOPP_MSGFPlusAdapter.html
